==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outgo
<hw>Out*go"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Outwent</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Outgone</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Outgoing</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To go beyond; to exceed in swiftness; to surpass; to
outdo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To circumvent; to overreach.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Denham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outgo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outgo
<hw>Out"go`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Outgoes</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>That which goes out, or is
paid out; outlay; expenditure; -- the opposite of <ant>income</ant>;
<as>as, when one's <ex>outgo</ex> exceeds one's income, distress follows
quickly</as>.</def> <rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outgoer</ent>⟦br⟧
